Chunks:
A diff won't show the entire contents of a file, but instead only shows portions
or "chunks" that were modified.

A chunk also indicates some unchanged lines before and after a change to provide
some context.

diff --git  a/rainbow.txt b/rainbow.txt -> File Compared
index 687578..fght785 18y78565  -> File Metadata
--- a/rainbow.txt -> Markers
+++ b/rainbow.txt -> Markers
@@ -3, 4 +3, 5 @@ orange -> Line 12 to line 19 is Chunks

yellow
green
blue
-purple
+indigo
+violet

